Title : Mahpahkum Indian Reserve No. 4
Text : '''Mahpahkum Indian Reserve No. 4''', officially '''Mahpahkum 4''', is an [[Indian reserve]] at the northwest end of [[Deserters Island]] in the [[Deserters Group]] of the [[Queen Charlotte Strait]] region of the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast of British Columbia]], Canada.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/65378.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Mahpahkum 4 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>  It is 7.8 hectares in size and is one of the reserves under the governance of the [[Gwa'Sala-Nakwaxda'xw]] [[band government]] of the [[Kwakwaka'wakw]] peoples.<ref>[http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/RVDetail.aspx?RESERVE_NUMBER=06996&lang=eng Indian and Northern Affairs Canada "Reserve/Settlement/Village Detail"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504103835/http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/RVDetail.aspx?RESERVE_NUMBER=06996&lang=eng |date=2014-05-04 }}</ref>

